node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Arley on September 06, 2021 tagging @xppen_ca. May be a cartoon of 1 person and text that says 'XP- XP-PEN CONTEST THEME: REDRAW YOUR OLD PAINTING WINNER RECEIVES AN ARTIST PRO 16 TABLET!'.

node.text:
YAAAYYY I’m hosting a contest with XP-PEN!!! ☺️🎉 All the contest details are in the slides so please make sure to read them if you plan on joining. In summary, you can redraw your old artwork, I’ll pick a winner out of the entries, and the winner receives an Artist Pro 16 tablet from XP-PEN! I love redraws because you get to see how much you’ve improved over time. I hope this becomes a fun learning experience for anyone who chooses to participate!
.
EDIT: “Additional Important Notes” has an underscore in xppenusa. There is NO underscore in the username for @xppenusa. Sorry for the confusion!!
.
The winner will be announced in my stories on Sept. 23rd (12:00 PM EDT). I will contact the winner via DMs to let them know they won. . If you have any questions, please leave them in the comments here. I’ll try my best to answer them but PLEASE keep in mind that it would be best to contact @xppenusa for any questions about shipping.
.
Also note that the Artist Pro 16 prize is a different tablet than the one I reviewed in my previous post. If you’d like to know more about it you can find it on XP-PEN’s website! .
I’m glad one of you will be able to get a tablet after this!! I hope you enjoy drawing! I’m SO EXCITED to see what you create!! 🙌
.
.
.
.
.
#collaboration #xppen16th #redrawoldpainting #xppen

node.text:
Thanks to @xppen_ca for sending me their Artist Pro 16TP to review! #gifted #collaboration I drew one of my original characters. I’ve made posts about him before but if this is your first time seeing him, this is Mason. He likes space, video games, and  r o c k s :D I loved working on the lighting for this artwork and it was honestly so refreshing to try out a new setup. .
.
If you’re interested, here are the product links to the official XP-PEN store: 👉US: https://www.storexppen.com/buy/16tp.html
👉CA: https://www.storexppen.ca/buy/16tp.html .
They also provided an extra 5% discount code! It can be used in conjunction with their 16th-Anniversary Sale in the US&CA stores.
👉 Code: PRO16TP .

node.text:
New hairdo from Butterboo 🤙 This is PART 2 of the Butch’s Bad Hair Day comic!! I really felt like the last comic needed another part so… ta-da lool. If you haven’t seen Part 1, you can find it in the Guides section on my profile under “Leechee’s PPG AU Comics pt. 2”
.
Side note: This was a very slight callback to an episode in the 1998 series where Buttercup (and Bubbles) gave Blossom and haircut and it ended up being a complete MESS. Things didn’t turn out as bad here and maybe Buttercup got a little bit of redemption pffft
.
I posted an alternate version of the first half of this comic with a few lines of Butch’s POV on Patreon (sweeeet and mmmm yessss tiers). I also posted wallpapers (mmmm yessss tier)
.
Another side note: shoutout to that one person in a past Q&A who joked about Butch looking like an axolotl in the last comic. I legit could not stop thinking about it. I found it SO accurate I HAD to include that on the first page 
.
.
.
.
.

Side note: I have no idea where I’m at in terms of plot and progress in this game since there’s A TON of things to do lmao. Anyways, I’m havin a good time! I’m either losing or gaining brain cells in shrines, cooking is surprisingly fun, and my favourite horse is named Carl :)
